===Etymology 1===
{{inh+|en|enm-nor|big}}, {{m|enm|bigge||powerful, strong}}, possibly from a dialect of {{der|en|non|-}}. Ultimately perhaps a derivative of {{der|en|gem-pro|*bugja-||swollen up, thick}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*bʰew-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*bu-||to swell}},<ref>{{R:ine:IEW|98-102}}</ref> in which case ''big'' would be related to {{m|en|[[bogey#Etymology_1|bogey]]}}, {{m|en|bugbear}}, and {{m|en|bug}}.

Compare dialectal {{cog|no|bugge|t=great man}}, {{cog|nds|Bögge}}, {{m|nds|Boggelmann}}.

